
Usage:
    scopy [options] ifn ofn

Synopsis:
    copy input file to output file making necessary convertions.

Options:
  -c, --compatibility       input is in SPro 3.x file format (no)
  -I, --bufsize=n           I/O buffer size in kbytes (10000)
  -i, --info                print stream information (off)
  -z, --suppress            suppress printing data (off)
  -B, --swap                swap byte order before writing new file (no)
  -o, --output-format=s     set output format (spro)
                            valid formats are: ascii, htk, sirocco

  -Z, --cms                 cepstral mean normalization
  -R, --normalize           variance normalization
  -L, --segment-length=n    segment length in frames for normalization (whole data)
  -D, --delta               add first order derivatives
  -A, --acceleration        add second order derivatives
  -N, --no-static-energy    remove static energy

  -m, --scale=f             scale features (no)
  -t, --transform=fn        apply transformation matrix in fn (none)
  -x, --extract=s           bin extraction pattern (none)

  -s, --start=n             starting at sample number (1)
  -e, --end=n               ending at sample number (last)

  -v, --verbose             verbose mode
  -V, --version             print version number
  -h, --help                this help message

